content: User has a useful option to increase the font. Sometimes the application increases the font, when the user just intent to prevent the screen go off. After returning the font to normal size the user cannot easy find the place, where his prayer was interrupted. It is very annoying during "tefilat amidah" (Shemona Esrei). It would be very useful to add the setting at which the user could selectively disable this feature.

It's overall a great app, however I found 2 minor issues: when I use it in landscape mode or zoom in, it's blurry for a few seconds, and the nasi that said on the phone screen now (in the month of nissan) is a broken link
replyContent:
Hi, 
We've forwarded your feedback to our developers. Thank you for taking out the time to send us your suggestions!

content: Siddur has a bug and scrambles paragraphs. Reading psukei d zimra and suddenly shmoneh esre appears and replaces next paragraphs. Happens throughout. Update: just uninstalled and reinstalled and looks like may have fixed problem. Other than this bug,, siddur is a pleasure to use and very good features.
replyContent: Hello. We've reset the data and everything should be in order now. Please check again. If the issue is not resolved for you or if you have any other concerns, please email us at appsupport@chabad.org.

content: clarity of continuity could be improved. format of isn't always the same as the Print version
